User_Message: What the hell is PrEP? Why the hell is this so complicated?
Response:
PrEP stands for pre-exposure prophylaxis. It is a medicine that helps prevent HIV. 

PrEP is for people who are at higher chance of getting HIV. It comes in two forms: daily pills or an injection every two months.

Using PrEP can lower your chance of getting HIV when taken as directed. Many find it helpful, but it can feel overwhelming at first. I'm here to help you understand it better!
